This is such a common thing to go through & can very easily become a feeling you struggle to escape. Being aware is the first step. Here’s what I like to do:

1. Take a productive day - turn on music & clean my spaces (taking breaks if I need to). Having a clean & peaceful place to rest is so important. 

2. Self care - take a candle lit bath, paint my nails, do my eyebrows, take a deep cleaning shower, mediate, whatever self care looks like for me. Just take care of myself. It makes me feel good physically which helps me feel better mentally.

3. Journal - writing out my feelings, patterns I have become aware of, what I would rather feel like & how to get there. Sometimes I am so mentally overwhelmed that I can’t write so I look up related journal prompts. Putting things in words out of my mind can be super beneficial. 

4. Movement - Sometimes training anyways or if I feel that I truly need rest, I’ll go for a nice walk after work. Any kind of movement can help clear my mind and make it easier to process my thoughts/feelings. 

5. Vent to a friend - just spilling my words and feelings to a safe friend always makes me feel lighter and hearing myself can be beneficial for awareness. 

6. Positive affirmations: As soon as I wake up, I try to affirmate. “I GET to do __,___,___.” (Things I don’t feel like doing), “I am worthy even when I am not feeling my best” “it is okay to not be okay” “the struggles are where I grow” “today is going to be a great day” “I will get through this” 

7. Eat clean - your gut health plays a large roll in your mood/mental health. I love to drink kombucha & eat clean foods that I love. I also value being a clean eater so it makes me feel good when I do. 
#mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #burnout #depression #anxiety #bjj #bjjlife #bjjcompetitor #grappling #grappler

HELLO 25!!! 🥳
••••••••••••••

My 24th year of life was unique - it had your typical hard times & some atypical but I became more unstoppable through the process. I spent a lot of time alone, learning about myself and focusing on what’s important to me. I had a successful competition year. I became an Aunt again x4. The last few months, I’ve felt myself enter a new era of my womanhood which makes me so excited to see what 25 has in store. 

My favorite part about 24 was meeting this man. He has done nothing but enrich my life since I met him almost a year ago. We’re building something beautiful & I express gratitude for it everyday. 🤎

Celebrating the 2023 year of SGC matches since we are 4 sleeps away from the last event of the year. 😈 Went a strong 5-0 #bjjladies #bjjlife #adcc #bluebelt #grappling #submissiongrappling #wrestling #boxing #martialartist #grappler #bjjcompetitor
Last training until showtime 🥰

Thats a wrap on 2023! 

This year really tested my jiu jitsu journey - challenges & big changes. It’s been tough to say the least but to say the most, it’s exactly what I needed. It forced me to think about how much I really love this sport, competing and why I do what I do. It tested me on how bad I truly want the goals that I have. 

I passed. Because I didn’t stop showing up. Were there times I didn’t go to the gym? Yes. Were there times I was feeling sorry for myself? Yes. But I never stopped. I took every battle & made the most that I could from each one, learning so much about myself, others & jiu jitsu as a whole. 

I’m taking every bit of that and using it to fuel 2024. I proved to myself how much I really want it so I’m going to go get it! You guys are amazing and your support always makes it so rewarding. I have a match planned for January 13 against a tough opponent! I’m going to be on social media significantly less so I can get my head in the game where it needs to be. I really love the person jiu jitsu has helped me become. ❤️

This was my first training after losing my match a few weeks ago. I was definitely hungry 🥰
